description:
Wildlife Instinct - Episode 1: Pallas's Cat - Master of the Plains | Free Nature Documentary

Watch "Wildlife Instincts: Survival Techniques - Iguana vs. Basilisk": https://youtu.be/4Ya0Niw0Rx8

The Great Plains of Mongolia is a land of extremes, and its inhabitants must adapt to severe changes in temperature. None is more suited to this unforgiving environment than the Pallass cat. These unique animals are able to change their shape with the seasons. But even for top predators, life isnt easy. Female Pallas cats must feed their growing families and pass on unique hunting techniques, as well as hiding skills, to ensure the young will make it to adulthood.
